The paper deals with distance oracles and compact routing in graphs, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed methods to routing in computer networks, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper involves the study of graph properties and connectivity, which is related to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper uses simulations to evaluate the proposed methods, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
